TANZANIA’s business magnate Mohammed Dewji has been ranked 15th among the top billionaires in the continent’s list released on Tuesday by the global business magazine–Forbes. Dewji’s fortune declined to an estimated $1.5 billion from $1.6 billion a year ago, due to lower multiples for publicly traded competitors. In the Forbes latest list that features 18 billionaires with fortunes estimated to reach $84.9billion named Nigerian billionaire Aliko Dangote as Africa’s richest man for the 11th year in a row.